    "id": 28,
    "post_url": "https://t.me/OSINTLive/520012",
    "text": "Visioner 🇺🇸 🇮🇷 A senior White House official described the two-week ceasefire as “a win” for President Trump to NewsNation, saying the president had always envisioned a “4–6 weeks” military operation and that U.S. forces “were exceptional and achieved our objectives.” The official added that “Iran no longer poses the threat they did 6 weeks ago\" and credited “tough negotiations” by Trump and JD Vance for securing both the ceasefire and a path toward a “workable diplomatic solution for long-term peace with Iran.” They also said “the Strait of Hormuz will reopen,” claiming Trump achieved this “without the help of NATO, despite the fact that they should have helped all along.” tweet",
